This model was modified several times, its record rate of fire was 1500 rounds per minute [17]. It was this sample that John Thompson demonstrated at Camp Perry in 1920. Some copies were made without stocks and sights, but the final version resembled a later one. 1921. It was this variant that was developed as a weapon for "cleansing" the trenches. The largest buyer was the New York Police Department; The weapon was produced not only under the standard 45 ACP cartridge, but also under the 22 Long Rifle [35], 32 ACP [35], 38 ACP [35] and 9 mm Parabellum [35] [19] types.